=begin pod

=head1 Slangify::Tutorial

yo

A tutorial demonstrating how to combine a Raku Grammar + Actions DSL with an
LLM pre-normalization step to extract structured data from free-form natural
language text.

=head2 Overview

The pipeline has two layers:

=item B<DSL layer> — C<Slangify::Tutorial::Grammar> parses a canonical mini-language directly.
This pair works standalone in the L<Grammar Editor|https://play.slangify.org> /
L<Slangify Playground|https://slangify.org>.

=item B<LLM layer> — C<bin/party-tute> accepts free-form English, uses C<LLM::Functions>
to normalize it to the canonical DSL form, then feeds it through the Grammar +
Actions pipeline.

=head2 Quick Start

=begin code :lang<raku>
use Slangify::Tutorial;

say parse-booking("Jane booked a table for 4 at 7:30pm tomorrow at Bistro Verde");
=end code

=head2 Installation

=begin code
zef install Slangify::Tutorial
=end code

=end pod
